---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Purpose" backLink="/" backText="Home" accentColor="#fb923c">

    <div class="header">
        <h1>Our Purpose</h1>
        <p>The heart, vision, and biblical mandate behind Keystone Youth.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="text-align: center; background: rgba(251, 146, 60, 0.1); border: 2px solid rgba(251, 146, 60, 0.3); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <h3 style="color: #fb923c; margin-top: 0; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 0.9rem;">Our Mission</h3>
        <p style="color: #ffffff; font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; margin: 0; line-height: 1.4;">"Inspiring youth to become fully devoted followers of Christ."</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left: 5px solid #facc15;">
        <h2 style="color: #f8fafc; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); padding-bottom: 10px; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.8rem;">🔗 Our Three Pillars</h2>
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.1rem; margin-top: 0;">To accomplish our mission, everything we do is built on helping students make three vital connections:</p>
        
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 20px 0 0 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 15px;">
            <li style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 15px; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: bold; color: #f8fafc; border-left: 4px solid #facc15;">
                <span style="font-size: 2rem;">✝️</span> Connect with Jesus
            </li>
            <li style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 15px; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: bold; color: #f8fafc; border-left: 4px solid #facc15;">
                <span style="font-size: 2rem;">🤝</span> Connect with Others
            </li>
            <li style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 15px; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: bold; color: #f8fafc; border-left: 4px solid #facc15;">
                <span style="font-size: 2rem;">⛪</span> Connect to the Local Church
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left: 5px solid #fb923c;">
        <h2 style="color: #f8fafc; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); padding-bottom: 10px; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.8rem;">🌍 Why Youth Events?</h2>
        <p style="color: #fb923c; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 1.2rem;">The Biblical Mandate for Service and Youth</p>
        
        <p style="color: #cbd5e1; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.1rem;">Serving within the local church is not merely a volunteer activity; it is the natural expression of the metaphor of the Body found in 1 Corinthians 12. Paul argues that "the eye cannot say to the hand, ‘I have no need of you’" (1 Corinthians 12:21), implying that every member, regardless of age, possesses a spiritual gift intended for the "common good" (12:7).</p>

        <p style="color: #cbd5e1; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.1rem;">When we serve, we move from being consumers of the Gospel to participants in the Great Commission (Matthew 28:19-20). For the youth, this is profoundly beneficial because it shifts their identity from being "the future of the church" to being active, vital members of the <em>present</em> church.</p>

        <p style="color: #cbd5e1; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.1rem;">By engaging in student service, they "stir up one another to love and good works" (Hebrews 10:24), which anchors their faith in action and protects them from the "drifting away" that often occurs when faith remains purely academic. Whether serving is leading a song, helping a younger peer, or participating in a challenge that illustrates a spiritual truth, it is all vital to their spiritual formation.</p>
    </div>

</BaseLayout>